1.25.24	Make sure that each of your computers connects to the network securely.	St
1.25.25	The laptop should connect via LAN (wired using Ethernet cable) and WLAN (wireless - Wi-Fi).	St
1.25.26	Purchase an external HD that is NAS (Network Attached Storage) capable using an Ethernet cable.	St
1.25.27	Once you plug in the NAS enabled HD to the back of your router it will be assigned a drive letter and appear in My Computer on each of your systems.	St
1.25.28	Using a backup utility software (Windows 7 has this feature built-in) you can schedule regular back-ups of your data to the external NAS HD from each computer or you can just drag and drop the files to it.	St
1.25.29	This option also best supports the use of two or more computers to share the same NAS drive.	St
1.25.30	Another option is to Partition the NAS HD.	St
1.25.31	Partitioning is where you divide the total capacity of the drive into (for example) half (i.e.	St
1.25.32	1TB HD drive split into two 500GB partitions).	St
1.25.33	Each 500GB partition will have its own drive letter.	St
1.25.34	You inturn would map Computer-A to a drive letter and Computer-B to the remaining drive letter.	St
1.25.35	In My Computer on Computer-A you will only see the drive letter you mapped (assigned) to it.	St
